Settings.QueryText: SELECT Files.BeingEditedBy, Files.CreationDate, Files.DeleteCurrentVersionVersionNumber, CAST(Files.Size / 1024 AS NUMBER(10, 0)) AS CurrentVersionSize, Files.Author, Files.Extension AS Extension, CASE WHEN Files.DeletionMark = TRUE THEN Files.PictureIndex + 1 ELSE Files.PictureIndex END AS PictureIndex, Files.Description, SUBSTRING(Files.Details, 0, 140) AS Details, Files.Ref, Files.DeletionMark, Files.StoreVersions, Files.FileOwner, Files.Changed AS WasEditedBy, CASE WHEN Files.BeingEditedBy = &CurrentUser THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE END AS CurrentUserEditsFile, CASE WHEN NOT Files.BeingEditedBy IN (&EmptyUsers) THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE END AS FileBeingEdited, Files.SignedWithDS AS SignedWithDS, Files.Encrypted AS Encrypted, CASE WHEN Files.SignedWithDS AND Files.Encrypted THEN 2 WHEN Files.Encrypted THEN 1 WHEN Files.SignedWithDS THEN 0 ELSE -1 END AS SignedEncryptedPictureNumber, DATEADD(Files.UniversalModificationDate, SECOND, &SecondsToLocalTime) AS ChangeDate, Files.Internal AS Internal, FilesEncoding.Encoding FROM Catalog.Files AS Files LEFT JOIN InformationRegister.FilesEncoding AS FilesEncoding ON Files.CurrentVersion = FilesEncoding.File WHERE (Files.FileOwner = &Owner OR NOT &UseHierarchy AND Files.FileOwner REFS Catalog.FilesFolders)

SELECT FilesFolders.Ref, FilesFolders.DeletionMark, FilesFolders.Predefined, FilesFolders.Parent, FilesFolders.Code, FilesFolders.Description, FilesFolders.Details, FilesFolders.EmployeeResponsible, FilesFolders.CreationDate, FilesFolders.Presentation, CASE WHEN FilesSynchronizationWithCloudServiceStatuses.File = FilesFolders.Ref THEN 2 WHEN FilesFolders.DeletionMark = TRUE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS PictureIndex, CASE WHEN FilesSynchronizationWithCloudServiceStatuses.File = FilesFolders.Ref THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE END AS FolderSynchronizationEnabled, FilesSynchronizationWithCloudServiceStatuses.Href, FilesSynchronizationWithCloudServiceStatuses.Account.Description, FilesSynchronizationWithCloudServiceStatuses.Account.Service, FilesSynchronizationWithCloudServiceStatuses.SynchronizationDateStart, FilesSynchronizationWithCloudServiceStatuses.Account AS Account, FilesSynchronizationWithCloudServiceStatuses.Synchronized FROM Catalog.FilesFolders AS FilesFolders LEFT JOIN InformationRegister.FilesSynchronizationWithCloudServiceStatuses AS FilesSynchronizationWithCloudServiceStatuses ON FilesFolders.Ref = FilesSynchronizationWithCloudServiceStatuses.File
